. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph de Picot Sheriff of Kent was born on 20 November 1110, in Milton, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, Roger FitzPicot de Saye, was 26 and his mother, Ethel de Bretagne, was 26. He married Ethelreda Port in 1146, in Milton, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. He died in 1165, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"20 November 1110–1165":"20. november 1110–1165","1110–1165":"1110–1165","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","1154–1184":"1154–1184","1155–1220":"1155–1220","1177–Female":"1177–Surnud","1085–1160":"1085–1160","1085–Female":"1085–Surnud","20 November 1110":"20. november 1110","1125":"1125","1146":"1146","1155":"1155","1177":"1177","1154":"1154","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1110":"1110","1085":"1085","1184":"1184","1160":"1160","Milton, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Milton, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tong Castle, Kent, England":"Tong Castle, Kent, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Milton, Kent, England":"Milton, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"20 November 1110–1165":"20. marraskuuta 1110–1165","1110–1165":"1110–1165","1125–Male":"1125–Kuollut","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","1154–1184":"1154–1184","1155–1220":"1155–1220","1177–Female":"1177–Kuollut","1085–1160":"1085–1160","1085–Female":"1085–Kuollut","20 November 1110":"20. marraskuuta 1110","1125":"1125","1146":"1146","1155":"1155","1177":"1177","1154":"1154","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1110":"1110","1085":"1085","1184":"1184","1160":"1160","Milton, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Milton, Ken